Estimation with linear regression model showed the best fit data of salmonellosis (P = 0.007), shigellosis (P < 0.001), and dengue (P < 0.001), while there was no significant linear trend was observed in the data of malaria (Fig. 2
). Pearson correlation showed a positive correlation between the number of outbound and inbound travelers and the number of imported cases of shigellosis, dengue, and the total number of imported infectious diseases (Table 2
, P < 0.001).
